0:07:24.259,0:07:26.470
Be careful with your words, Lorenzo.

0:07:27.240,0:07:30.370
You might attract the wrong sort of attention.

0:09:02.500,0:09:03.579
GUEST 1: Good evening, Gonfalionere.

0:09:05.889,0:09:08.629
UBERTO: To you as well. I trust you're enjoying yourselves?

0:09:09.299,0:09:13.049
GUEST 1: Indeed, a nice distraction from that nasty business with the Auditore family.

0:09:13.139,0:09:16.129
UBERTO: And to think I once thought of Giovanni as a brother.

0:09:18.179,0:09:20.189
GUEST: Don't blame yourself.

0:09:20.190,0:09:21.689
GUEST 1: How could you have known what evils he planned?

0:09:21.690,0:09:25.899
GUEST 2: I say we strike that traitor's name from the record books.

0:09:25.899,0:09:28.299
GUEST 2: Let history forget he ever even existed.

0:09:29.529,0:09:32.750
UBERTO: Hmm, yes. If you'll excuse me for a moment.

0:09:43.899,0:09:45.639
BEATRICE: Uberto, a moment of your time?

0:09:45.639,0:09:47.370
UBERTO: Anything for you, Beatrice.

0:09:50.889,0:09:55.559
BEATRICE: So tell us, how does it feel to be a hero?

0:09:55.809,0:09:56.829
UBERTO: Please, I am no such thing.

0:09:56.830,0:10:06.500
UBERTO: As Gonfaloniere it is my duty to ensure that
the city of Firenze remains a shining beacon of justice.

0:10:06.649,0:10:13.038
UBERTO: Corruption and its ilk shall find
no purchase here so long as I am in control.

0:10:13.039,0:10:17.119
BEATRICE: You are a treasure, Uberto. I hope Lorenzo recognises that.

0:10:17.120,0:10:20.409
UBERTO: Yes, our great leader Lorenzo. [coughs]

0:10:22.889,0:10:24.850
UBERTO: I will see you ladies later.

0:10:40.309,0:10:41.459
GUEST 3: Ah, Uberto, there you are.

0:10:41.460,0:10:44.490
GUEST 3: I was just telling the others about the execution.

0:10:44.590,0:10:51.429
GUEST 4: I mean no offence, but what if they did not act alone?
UBERTO: You can rest easy, friends.

0:10:51.429,0:10:57.009
UBERTO: I am confident that this treachery began and ended with the Auditore family.

0:10:57.529,0:10:59.029
GUEST 5: What of the other son, Ezio was it?

0:11:01.870,0:11:07.009
UBERTO: The child poses no danger. Soft hands and an even softer head.

0:11:07.419,0:11:10.700
UBERTO: He'll be caught and executed before the week is out.

0:11:11.149,0:11:15.320
GUEST 3: Don't let us keep you, Uberto. We just wanted to say hello.

0:11:23.950,0:11:24.548
GUEST 4: Evening to you, Gonfaloniere.

0:11:24.549,0:11:28.850
UBERTO: Is everything to your satisfaction?

0:11:28.970,0:11:31.749
GUEST 4: Do you even need to ask? Of course!

0:11:31.750,0:11:37.320
GUEST 5: Accept our thanks, for this evening and for helping to keep Firenze safe.

0:11:37.419,0:11:40.070
GUEST 5: I always had my doubts about the Auditore.

0:11:40.070,0:11:42.399
GUEST 5: Where did the family even come from?

0:11:42.639,0:11:52.360
GUEST 5: To gain such wealth and–and prestige in just a single generation.
GUEST 4: And the children, with their odd names, always making trouble.

0:11:52.379,0:11:55.159
GUEST 5: No surprise given the company that father kept.

0:11:55.899,0:11:58.389
GUEST 5: Whores and thieves I swear it.

0:11:59.070,0:12:06.620
UBERTO: Indeed, it is clear now he sought to undermine the city.
UBERTO: To overturn all we've worked so hard to build.

0:12:06.730,0:12:09.129
