Madre (Mother)?

0:21:46.240,0:21:51.118
Ezio! Where have you been?
They wouldn't let us leave.

0:21:51.119,0:21:54.568
And mother, oh! She hasn't spoken a single word since we left the house.

0:21:54.569,0:21:56.649
Father will need to sort things out.

0:21:56.650,0:21:59.239
Where is Father, and Federico, and Petruccio? Hmm?

0:22:03.190,0:22:05.869
Something's happened.

0:22:06.099,0:22:07.390
What do you mean?

0:22:09.349,0:22:11.399
No, it's impossible!

0:22:11.400,0:22:12.288
Claudia.

0:22:12.289,0:22:14.118
No! No, no, no, no!

0:22:14.119,0:22:15.859
I did everything I could, piccina (little one).

0:22:23.839,0:22:26.980
Listen! Right now, what matters is getting us all someplace safe.

0:22:27.140,0:22:30.480
But to do that, I need you to stay focused.

0:22:30.539,0:22:32.039
Do you understand?

0:22:37.720,0:22:39.490
Good, will you watch over mother for me?

0:22:45.210,0:22:48.670
Then we are ready. Thank you again for everything.

0:22:49.809,0:22:53.149
Stay safe, Ezio, stay vigilant.

0:22:53.150,0:22:55.779
I suspect the road ahead is yet long.

0:23:02.140,0:23:03.160
EZIO: On me.

0:26:53.809,0:26:55.999
CLAUDIA: How could this have happened to us?

0:26:56.000,0:26:57.349
EZIO: I don't know.

0:27:11.339,0:27:12.939
CLAUDIA: Will we ever be back?

0:27:12.940,0:27:14.490
EZIO: I don't know.

0:27:47.740,0:27:49.828
CLAUDIA: What will happen to our house?

0:27:49.829,0:27:51.429
EZIO: I don't know!

0:27:51.430,0:27:54.859
CLAUDIA: Were they… Were they given a proper burial?

0:27:55.640,0:27:58.160
EZIO: Yes, they were.

0:28:40.950,0:28:42.319
EZIO: We should be close.
CLAUDIA: Grazie Dio (Thank God)!

0:28:50.740,0:28:52.349
Buongiorno, Ezio.

0:28:54.039,0:28:57.868
How could you leave Firenze without saying a proper goodbye?

0:28:57.869,0:28:58.779
CLAUDIA: Ezio!

0:28:59.309,0:29:03.890
What do you want, Vieri?
So many things.

0:29:04.440,0:29:11.160
A larger palazzo, two new steeds, A prettier bride…

0:29:11.690,0:29:14.950
Oh, and yes, your life.

0:29:15.900,0:29:17.950
VIERI: My condolences for the—

0:29:20.630,0:29:22.869
VIERI: —loss of your father and brothers.

0:29:23.559,0:29:26.660
VIERI: What will happen now that there's no one left to help you?

0:29:27.029,0:29:31.279
VIERI: I have such wonderful things in store for your mother and sister.

0:29:37.400,0:29:39.789
I grow tired of this game.

0:29:40.839,0:29:43.829
Finish him, and do not spare the women!

0:29:45.539,0:29:47.660
What's sorcery is this?

0:29:48.740,0:29:49.749
VOICE: Ha ha ha ha! Not sorcery, boy, skill.

0:29:49.750,0:29:54.339
Show yourself!
VOICE: As you wish.

0:29:55.440,0:29:56.588
VOICE: Here, use this!

0:29:56.589,0:29:59.619
Kill them! Kill them all!

0:31:04.240,0:31:05.749
You have my thanks.

0:31:05.750,0:31:07.450
Keep the sword, Ezio.

0:31:07.839,0:31:09.660
Do I know you from somewhere?

0:31:10.140,0:31:14.049
Don't you recognise me? It's-a-me, Mario!

0:31:14.289,0:31:15.720
Uncle Mario?!

0:31:15.930,0:31:19.160
It's been too long, nipote (nephew), far too long.

0:31:20.039,0:31:24.349
I heard what happened in Firenze, terrible.

0:31:24.650,0:31:27.549
Come, let's get you all away from here.

0:32:57.440,0:32:59.950
MARIO: So, tell me everything.

0:33:00.240,0:33:02.549
EZIO: They executed father for treason.

0:33:02.990,0:33:05.069
EZIO: Federico and Petrucci too.

0:33:05.640,0:33:07.259
EZIO: Then they came for me.

0:33:07.309,0:33:08.849
MARIO: Do you know why?

0:33:09.640,0:33:14.779
EZIO: I have no answers uncle, only a list of names taken from a man who wished me dead.

0:33:14.799,0:33:16.699
EZIO: I still can't believe they're gone.

0:33:16.700,0:33:19.669
MARIO: Don't worry, we will make sense of this.

0:33:19.670,0:33:21.739
EZIO: I wish I shared your optimism.

0:33:21.740,0:33:30.999
MARIO: I think you will find much to like in Monteriggioni.
EZIO: I thought Monteriggioni was an enemy of Firenze?
MARIO: For now. Next year it will be its friend. 

0:33:31.000,0:33:32.639
MARIO: The year after, its enemy again, and on, and on.

0:33:34.269,0:33:37.259
MARIO: I cannot keep track, so I've stopped trying.

0:33:37.339,0:33:40.170
MARIO: These are honest, hardworking people.

0:33:40.190,0:33:45.139
MARIO: Our shops may only carry simple goods, but they're well made and dependable.

0:33:45.140,0:33:46.989
MARIO: There's a chapel here too.

0:33:46.990,0:33:52.339
MARIO: prete (priest) seems a nice enough fellow,
but I've never been much of a believer.

0:33:53.029,0:33:57.038
MARIO: Did you know the Villa Auditore is almost 200 years old?

0:33:57.039,0:34:02.500
MARIO: It was built by my great-grandfather, a strange man who carried all kinds of secrets.

0:34:02.609,0:34:06.349
MARIO: Keep your eyes open and you might discover a few of them yourself.

0:34:06.440,0:34:12.789
MARIO: With all the fighting that's been going on, this place has started to get a bit rough around the edges.

0:34:12.889,0:34:17.960
MARIO: I wish I could do something about it, but I just don't have the time or money to fix things up.

0:34:18.039,0:34:19.590
MARIO: Guess that's life, huh?

0:34:20.559,0:34:23.349
MARIO: Here we are, casa dolce casa (home sweet home).

0:34:23.639,0:34:25.789
MARIO: So what do you think?

0:34:26.539,0:34:28.398
EZIO: It's most impressive, Uncle.

0:34:28.400,0:34:31.110
MARIO: She's seen better days, I suppose.

0:34:31.139,0:34:35.960
MARIO: Believe me, I'd have her shining again if only I had the time.

0:34:36.210,0:34:40.528
MARIO: Now that you have had the tour nipote, you should go and outfit yourself.

0:34:40.530,0:34:43.608
MARIO: My men in the market are expecting you.

0:34:43.610,0:34:46.059
MARIO: Return here when you're finished and we'll begin.

0:34:46.309,0:34:48.759
EZIO: "Begin"? Begin what?

0:34:48.760,0:34:51.050
MARIO: I thought you'd come here to train.

0:34:51.199,0:34:52.440
EZIO: No, uncle, I came here to escape Firenze, and I intend to take my family further still.

0:34:57.940,0:35:01.738
MARIO: But what about your father? He'd want you to finish his work.

0:35:01.739,0:35:04.738
EZIO: What work? My father was a banker.

0:35:04.739,0:35:07.118
MARIO: Wait, he did not tell you?

0:35:07.119,0:35:09.538
EZIO: I have no idea what you're talking about.

0:35:09.539,0:35:12.110
MARIO: Ma che mi combini (What were you thinking), Giovanni?!

0:35:13.039,0:35:14.849
MARIO: Where to even begin.

0:35:15.000,0:35:17.009
MARIO: Go and fetch the gear in the market.

0:35:17.010,0:35:22.300
MARIO: It will give me time to think.
EZIO: But– 
MARIO: But that's that. We'll talk more later.

0:35:22.380,0:35:24.688
MARIO: Some spending money should you need it.

0:35:24.690,0:35:30.550
MARIO: And if you find yourself in need of rest, I've prepared a room for you on the top floor of the villa.

